snippet: Thousands of athletes braved temperatures in the 90s and swam down the Hudson River, cycled along the Henry Hudson Parkway and ran through Central Park as part of the New York City Triathlon on Sunday.
abstract: Photos of athletes competing in New York City Triathlon; Ben Collins wins men's professional division in 1 hour 44 minutes and 59 seconds, while Alicia Kaye takes women's professional division in 1:58:25.
lead_paragraph: Thousands of athletes braved temperatures in the 90s and swam down the Hudson River, cycled along the Henry Hudson Parkway and ran through Central Park as part of the New York City Triathlon on Sunday.

headline.main: They Could’ve Used a Swim at the End, Too
